Appearance
From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

This article contains a list of all scheduled matches to be played during the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific regular season. The draw for the 31st season of Super Rugby was released on 28 August 2025,[1] with several key fixture announcements made in the weeks before. Similar to last season, each team will play fourteen fixtures and have two byes throughout the season.[1] Each team will play a domestic "rival" team twice on a home-and-away basis, with their remaining fixtures being against non-domestic teams.[1] The 2026 season did not include "Culture Round" or "Kids Round"; however, there was a convergence of two significant rugby events, "ANZAC Weekend Round" and "Super Round" (as in 2022), into a single weekend, held at the newly constructed Te Kaha stadium in Christchurch, New Zealand.[2][3][4]

The season formally begins on 13 February 2026 and is set to finish on 30 May 2026 before the start of the 2026 Finals series.[1]

Notes

[edit]
  1. ^ a b c d e f The venue for the Blues home fixtures in the 2026 season wasn't yet known at the time the schedule for the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific season was released. On 4 September 2025, the Blues announced that their home games would take place at Eden Park, Auckland.[5]
  2. ^ The venue for the round 5 match between the Hurricanes and the Force on 13 March 2026 wasn't yet known at the time the schedule for the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific season was released. On 9 October 2025, the Hurricanes announced that the game would be played at McLean Park, Napier.[6]
  3. ^ The venue for the round 9 match between the Drua and the Force on 11 April 2026 wasn't yet known at the time the schedule for the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific season was released. On 13 November 2025, the Drua announced that the game would be played at Churchill Park, Lautoka.[7]
  4. ^ The venue for the round 12 match between the Drua and the Highlanders on 2 May 2026 wasn't yet known at the time the schedule for the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific season was released. On 13 November 2025, the Drua announced that the game would be played at 4R Electrical Govind Park, Ba.[7]
  5. ^ The venue for the round 14 match between the Drua and the Hurricanes on 16 May 2026 wasn't yet known at the time the schedule for the 2026 Super Rugby Pacific season was released. On 8 September 2025, the Drua announced that the game would be played at HFC Bank Stadium, Suva.[8]
